## API Endpoint

### Get Rewards by Customer ID

```http
GET /api/rewards/{customerId}
```

### Example Request

```http
GET /api/rewards/101
```

### Example Response

```json
{
  "customerId": 101,
  "customerName": "John",
  "monthlyRewards": {
    "January": 90,
    "February": 25,
    "March": 150
  },
  "totalRewards": 265
}
```

---

## Implementation Details

### Reward Calculation Logic

The reward calculation is implemented in:

```text
RewardCalculator.java
```

### Rules Applied

```java
if (amount > 100) {
    points += (amount - 100) * 2;
    points += 50;
} else if (amount > 50) {
    points += amount - 50;
}
```

### Dynamic Month Calculation

Months are not hardcoded.

Month names are dynamically generated using:

```java
transactionDate.getMonth()
               .getDisplayName(TextStyle.FULL, Locale.ENGLISH)
```

This satisfies the requirement:

**Do not hardcode the months**

---

## Database Configuration

The project uses:

```text
H2 In-Memory Database
```

This helps:

* easy local testing
* no external database setup
* faster execution
* simplified demonstration for interview assignment

### H2 Console

```http
http://localhost:8080/h2-console
```

### Login Details

| Property | Value                 |
| -------- | --------------------- |
| JDBC URL | jdbc:h2:mem:rewardsdb |
| Username | sa                    |
| Password | (blank)               |

